&lt;pre&gt;Hi Tom, the team is working both with Chrome Security and in the W3C WebML
CG (see P&amp;S considerations
&lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://github.com/webmachinelearning/webmcp/blob/main/docs/security-privacy-considerations.md"&gt;https://github.com/webmachinelearning/webmcp/blob/main/docs/security-privacy-considerations.md&lt;/a&gt;&gt;)
to figure out these challenges, with bi-weekly CG meetings where security
and privacy questions are actively being discussed. I agree that there is a
lot we have to get right here, and we'll involve TAG and others for help
and review as per the process. Note that this is an early prototype for
developer testing and not an intent to to ship.&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;pre&gt;

I'm happy to join any SING call if you'd like to discuss this further.

Thanks!

Johann

