&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Explainer
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://jpeg.org/jpegxl/"&gt;https://jpeg.org/jpegxl/&lt;/a&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="http://ds.jpeg.org/whitepapers/jpeg-xl-whitepaper.pdf"&gt;http://ds.jpeg.org/whitepapers/jpeg-xl-whitepaper.pdf&lt;/a&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Specification&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1908.03565"&gt;https://arxiv.org/abs/1908.03565&lt;/a&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Summary
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; JPEG XL is a new royalty-free image codec targeting the image quality
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; as found on the web, providing about ~60% size savings when compared to
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; original JPEG at the same perceptual quality, while supporting modern
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; features like HDR, animation, alpha channel, lossless JPEG recompression,
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; lossless and progressive modes. It is based on Google's PIK and
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Cloudinary's FUIF, and is in the final steps of standardization with ISO.
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; This feature enables image/jxl decoding support in the blink renderer
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Blink componentBlink&gt;Image
